The paper deals with detecting credential stuffing attacks, which is a common security threat in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed framework involves anomaly detection and tracking suspicious logins, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses a private membership-test protocol, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SE).
